      <div class="msgContentFrame">I havent seen anyone mention this yet and to me it's pretty important. It didnt even dawn on me until some one mentioned it in an LS. I used to put all my points into fire elemental then after awhile I started mixing them up, but all I would get is fire shards while mining or Botany. I've reset my stats several times and since I realized that it affects what shard you get i've pushed my earth and wind higher (fire is still up there though, takes awhile to reset when there is a big chunk in one stat), as of now I get more of a mix between fire, wind and earth. <br /> <br />Maybe this is common knowledge, but I havent seen this discussed anywhere on the forums. <br /> <br />I would say elemental stats, when mining or botany, are like a percentage, if they are all at 30 or whatever then you'll randomly get what ever shard. If you have one way higher then the others then thats all you'll get. What I'm not sure yet is if you have high elemental stats if you get more of that certain shard or more often or what.  <br /> <br />I've seen talk about crystals while mining/ botany and some say they've got them, but most say they havent. It wouldn't surprise me if you had a specific elemental stat really high that you may start seeing crystals. My phsical level is probably not high enough to test that, but might be worth trying (though it could be a lot of resets for some one).</div>
